    "Html": "<p>Hi Rick,</p>\r\n<p>I have noticed that you are not using any Canvas in the ItemsControl template, but still you are setting the Canvas.TopProperty in the view. If you do use a Canvas in the template, you should make sure the view is a direct child (first child of it), and set the property using <strong>this</strong> instead of <strong>Stack</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>If you have any other questions related to this, you might get a better answer in the <a href=\"http://forums.silverlight.net/forums/\">Silverlight forums</a>, as this is not directly Prism related (since you are not using Regions) and the community is used to answering Silverlight specific questions.</p>\r\n<p id=92d366a0-8ff4-012c-e1c8-12313b002471>Please let me know if this helps.</p>\r\n<p id=92d39ac0-8ff4-012c-e1c9-12313b002471>Damian Schenkelman    <br><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman\">http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman</a></p>",
